Question: How do you believe ACME should better support organizations and cultural leaders?

Response ID: resp_2379
Response Text: City grants are absolutely vital for small but longstanding organizations to survive in Austin. We just don't have the foundations other major cities have and the ones we do are more and more going to invite only applications. 

I really loved part of how the last round of your grant program sought to repair major issues and build here, but I'm also VERY happy you are assessing the holes that program had around not supporting long-standing or artistically-impactful organizations that might not have been able to hit the highest point answers on those scoring systems. 

It would be great if you all helped build community among the arts nonprofits in the city. We do that ourselves, but it can be hard. I think communication WITH and facilitating connection BETWEEN the people creating the arts community here has to be a part of the plan. 

Venues (even churches) are really jacking up rents - I get it...but it's hard for arts groups to make it.

